text: When using the snipping tool I’ve always used “windows button + shift + s” and your screen should turn grey and your cursor becomes a cross, you can then drag and draw a square to draw out your snip shape

text: Hey Armando, Great Question! You can set the Size and Position in Microsoft Word. Once you take a screenshot with the Snipping Tool and pasted it in the Word Document, right-click on the image and select Size and Position.

elements.text: Hey Armando, Great Question! You can set the Size and Position in Microsoft Word. Once you take a screenshot with the Snipping Tool and pasted it in the Word Document, right-click on the image and select Size and Position.
